name: /select_no_var
description:
This API endpoint tracks pull request (PR) activities across GitHub repositories that are part of a specified collection. It compares PR data over two selected time periods, providing insights into:

The total number of pull requests made.
The growth of pull requests in the current period compared to the previous period.
The ranking of each repository by the number of pull requests in the current period.
The percentage change in the total number of pull requests from one period to the next.
The change in rank position between the two periods for each repository.
The endpoint is flexible to analyze either the past month or a span of 56 days, allowing users to gauge the momentum and collaborative progress within the collection's repositories.
